\begin{align} p-1&\equiv-1\\ &\equiv(p-1)!\qquad\text{(by Wilson's Theorem)}\\ &=(p-1)(p-2)(p-3)!\\ &\equiv(-1)(-2)(p-3)!\\ &=2(p-3)!\\ \end{align}
